        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.longandshort.com/email/images/ls-jan-27-2.jpg" alt="CHART" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Programmatic advertising revenue reached $114.2 billion in 2023, marking a 4.4% year-over-year increase. This growth came slower compared to previous years. Non-programmatic placements also experienced significant growth, rising from $16.0 billion in 2022 to $22.0 billion in 2023.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">From 2019 to 2023, programmatic revenues nearly doubled, but growth is now tapering. Conversely, the rise in non-programmatic revenues underscores a diversification in digital ad strategies as advertisers look beyond programmatic solutions to optimize their campaigns.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Despite the slower growth in programmatic advertising, the combined total of programmatic and non-programmatic revenues reached $136.2 billion in 2023, highlighting the continued dominance of digital ad spending.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
