            <strong>🇨🇳 China’s growing power demand challenges climate goals</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
          The rising demand for more electricity in China is challenging <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-27-01-2025-wn2-4-global-climate-efforts" target="_blank">global climate efforts</a>. Electricity use grew 6.8% last year, outpacing overall economic growth at the highest clip in at least 15 years, prompting the country to burn more coal. Even after record additions of wind turbines and solar panels, the country burned 1.5% more coal than in 2023. The biggest driver of this elevated power demand has been biopharmaceuticals, airplanes, solar panels, and EVs.
        </p>
