          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
          BYD is planning to launch <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-27-01-2025-wn3-plug-in-hybrid-vehicles" target="_blank">plug-in hybrid vehicles</a> in Japan. Battery-powered cars remain a small minority in Japan, and BYD wants to test the market before launching more EVs in the country. The Chinese automaker only sold 2,200 vehicles in Japan last year, which is still a 50% increase. BYD is set to launch the Sealion 7 crossover in Japan from April 2025. The firm is reportedly planning to invest $721 million to set up a facility with a production capacity of 150,000 vehicles per year.
