        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>The rise of AI boosts electricity demand in the US:</strong> The rise of AI has increased the energy demand. The top US power grid is expected to see a <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-27-01-2025-m2-7-38-rise-in-demand" target="_blank">38% rise in demand</a> over the next decade. The energy required to power data centers and computing infrastructure is growing rapidly and is straining energy outputs around the world. At Davos this week, Trump said power plants must be built alongside data centers to bypass delays and reliability issues posed by connecting to an increasingly stressed grid.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>UnitedHealth Cyberattack affects 190 million people:</strong> UnitedHealth revealed that the <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-27-01-2025-m3-8-cyberattack-on-its-tech" target="_blank">cyberattack on its tech</a> unit last year affected the information of about 190 million people. The data comprised includes social security numbers, health insurance IDs, and even billing codes used by payment providers. The attack is expected to cost UnitedHealth from $2.3 billion to $2.5 billion. It made at least one ransomware payment of roughly $22 million.</p>
